anguage=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2113<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/26/02 9:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=546.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/devil.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What's your stance on a chemical HLV?</span><hr size=1> It's better than nothing. The last time we did it was for Apollo. Look how that ended up. Nuclear would be preferable. It's time for a change. Chemical rockets have had their day in my opinion. I really don't know if I would vote for my tax dollars going into a Sea Dragon. I have lost all confidence in chemical rockets achieving anything worthwhile. To date they have done nothing.<br>
Orbiting aged modules hobbled together and called an ISS. Tossing tiny tin cans at the outer system and watching them take decades to arrive. Telecommunications satellites. None of these get us any closer to personal space vehicles, holidays on Mars, O'Neil colonies. Chem is a joke. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 1109<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/27/02 8:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=546.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What's your stance on a chemical HLV?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I really don't know if I would vote for my tax dollars going into a Sea Dragon.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
